Description: 2003 Gibson Les Paul Historic Brazilian R0 1960 Reissue. Serial # 0 3090 Weight: 9.2 lbs An absolutely beautiful Custom Shop guitar in a unique TAK burst. Given the moniker “The Chameleon”, this beautifully book matched maple top changes its color tones under different lighting situations. A real player with low string action and tone and the frets are in excellent condition. 2003 was the last year Gibson used Brazilian fretboards for some time. The tone from these Brazilian boards are amazing as they were used in the original 50’s and 60 vintage Les Paul Guitars. It also boasts a brand new wiring harness by Jackson Luthier out of Texas with Russian paper in oil capacitors. In addition, it has Vintage late 1960 Gibson T-Top Patent Number/Sticker pickups with nickel covers. Both have a DC reading at 7.64K resistance. The pickups are worth $800 alone. They are vintage and sound incredible. Think Jimmy Page, Angus Young, Paul Kossof. Also comes with the Historic Gibson hardshell case. Check out the 50 photos above taken under different lighting.
